<!-- BootStrap How-To Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="howToModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel">
  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-body">
      <!-- Google Card -->
        <div class="mdl-card mdl-shadow--2dp demo-card-wide">
          <div class="mdl-card__title">
            <h6 class="mdl-card__title-text">how does this work?</h6>
          </div>
          <div class="mdl-card__supporting-text">
          <!-- <h6 id="aboutData" >About This Application (especially the data)</h6> -->
          <ul>
            <li>In the first section, choose a subset of data to work with. For instance, if you wanted to study player careers with more than 5518 rebounds, select 'player_careers' from the 'select data' drop-down, 'reb' from the 'select metric' drop-down, '>' (more than) from the 'choose operation' drop-down, and 5518 from the values drop-down.</li>

            <li>In the second section, choose basketball metrics to visualize. Click "Choose X and Y Axes" to specify along which metrics you'd like to visualize the data subset you've chosen. The choice of metrics for the x- and y-axes come from the data table you've chosen. </li>

            <li>The visualization will re-render with changes to the x- and y-axes. If you adjust the data subset you're working with, click "Choose X and Y Axes" again to reset the axes choices. (In the future I may make the re-render of the visuals responsive as well to adjustments in the data subset dropdowns.)

            <li>Using the player_regular_seasons table takes longer (or may not work) right now. This is a known issue I'm working on rectifying.</li>
          </ul>
            Have fun!

            -Eric

          </div>
          <div class="mdl-card__actions mdl-card--border">
            <a data-dismiss="modal" class="mdl-button mdl-button--colored mdl-js-button mdl-js-ripple-effect">
              got it
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- end google card -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- Bootstrap About Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="aboutModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel">
  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-body">
      <!-- Google Card -->
        <div class="mdl-card mdl-shadow--2dp demo-card-wide">
          <div class="mdl-card__title">
            <h6 class="mdl-card__title-text">about this application</h6>
          </div>
          <div class="mdl-card__supporting-text">
          <!-- <h6 id="aboutData" >About This Application (especially the data)</h6> -->
          <ul>
            <li>Data graciously provided at no charge for research/educational purposes at <a href="http://basketballreference.com/stats_download.htm">databaseBasketball.com</a>. Data is as accurate as they have made it. Learn more about the data itself <a href='http://basketballreference.com/about/aboutplayerstats.htm'>here</a>.</li>

            <li>DreamTeam is intended as a research tool for basketball statistics. The data is from 1946-2009.</li>

            <li>As not every metric offered in this application was tracked by the/a league in every one of those years, some data subsets will contain lots of zeros, and this will necessarily affect the visualizations sometimes.</li> 

            <li>Some tables do not contain numerical data - non-numerical data will not show up in visualizations.</li> 

            <li>DreamTeam has been constructed to allow maximum user flexibility in how a data visualization is built. Many visualizations - e.g.: field goals attempted (fga) vs. field goals made (fgm) - will make real-world basketball-sense. Others - e.g.: assists by the opposing team (d_asts) vs. personal fouls by the offense (o_pf) - arguably may not ... but you can still visualize them anyhow and draw your own conclusions from what you find.</li>

          </ul>
            Have fun!

            -Eric

          </div>
          <div class="mdl-card__actions mdl-card--border">
            <a data-dismiss="modal" class="mdl-button mdl-button--colored mdl-js-button mdl-js-ripple-effect">
              got it
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- end google card -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
